# COMPILER/BOOT/iii_ring_lattice.def
#
# SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for the KATABASIS legal ring-transition lattice
# (DOCS/III-KATABASIS.md plan 4.6).  Descending beneath the OS crosses CPU
# privilege rings; III permits a crossing ONLY through one of the lawful
# constructors (no ring skipped, none ascended without the proper door).  This
# table is the relation: ordered (src, dst) ring pair -> the single legal
# constructor.
#
# Regenerate the AUTO-GENERATED constructor cascade in
# STDLIB/iii/katabasis/ring_lattice.iii via:
#     bash COMPILER/BOOT/gen_ring_lattice.sh
# The build's drift gate (gen_ring_lattice.sh --check) fails on divergence
# (plan 6.9 / FR-9).
#
# The classifier encodes the pair as key = src_code*5 + dst_code over the ring
# codes R3=0 R0=1 RM1=2 RM2=3 RM4=4 (a flat key cascade is exact).  Each row maps
# to the hand-written enum constants in ring_lattice.iii:
#   ring code const = KRL_<ring>          (e.g. KRL_R3, KRL_RM1)
#   constructor const = KRL_C_<ctor>      (e.g. KRL_C_IOCTL)
# gen_ring_lattice.sh asserts those constants exist; any (src,dst) NOT listed
# here maps to KRL_C_NONE (the catch-all -- no ring may be skipped or ascended).
#
# Rows are emitted in this order (matches the existing cascade).
#
# Fields (whitespace-delimited):  src  dst  constructor
#   src   str -- source ring (R3|R0|RM1|RM2|RM4); forms KRL_<src>.
#   dst   str -- destination ring; forms KRL_<dst>.
#   ctor  str -- the legal constructor; forms KRL_C_<ctor>.
# Lines starting with '#' are comments. Blank lines ignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# src  dst   constructor
R3     R0    IOCTL
R0     RM1   MAGIC_MSR
RM1    RM1   VMRUN
R0     RM2   SKINIT
RM1    RM2   SMI
